<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<CONTENT id="_3793144_1"><TITLE value="Session 4"/><TITLECOLOR value="#000000"/><DESCRIPTION
   value=""/><BODY><TEXT>&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;img src="@X@EmbeddedFile.requestUrlStub@X@bbcswebdav/xid-46885301_1" alt="" width="695" height="269" style="border: 0px solid #000000;"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h5&gt;News&lt;/h5&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1.&lt;span style="font-size: 12pt;"&gt; &lt;a href="https://ia.acs.org.au/article/2025/-undercooked---scam-reforms-rushed-through-parliament.html?ref=newsletter&amp;amp;deliveryName=DM25315" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;‘Undercooked’: Scam reforms rushed through Parliament | Information Age | ACS&amp;nbsp;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.patreon.com/posts/china-is-able-to-97117181?utm_medium=post_notification_email&amp;amp;utm_campaign=patron_engagement&amp;amp;utm_source=post_link" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;&lt;span style="text-decoration: underline;"&gt;2.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style="font-size: 12pt;"&gt;ThreatWire 25 Jan 2024 | Patreon&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; watch until end of 3rd story - 4 min total&lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Threatwire&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt; a weekly video podcast which has a number of stories each week on hacking and other cyber security related events. Although USA based, it is still a good source of the nature of current threats and the failures that allowed them to succeed.&lt;br&gt;This weeks stories are&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;USA Security and Exchange Commission (SEC) X-account hacked via a SIM swapping attack and because its 2FA was switched off&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;USA IT pen tester gets found guilty and fined for unauthorised penetration testing despite uncovering a very serious vulnerability of the target company&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;China uni develops a way of revealing the senders, recipients and contents of Airdrop (Apple to Apple wireless file transfer method)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;p&gt;3. &lt;a href="https://ia.acs.org.au/article/2024/should-i-give-my-banking-password-to-a-mortgage-broker-.html?ref=newsletter&amp;amp;deliveryName=DM23027" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 12pt;"&gt;Should I give my banking password to a mortgage broker? | Information Age | ACS&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp; - "Screen scraping" Vs Open Banking with Consumer Data Rights (CDR)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;4. &lt;span style="font-size: 12pt;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://ia.acs.org.au/article/2024/cyber-company-duped-by-north-korean-hacker.html?ref=newsletter&amp;amp;deliveryName=DM23027" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;Cyber company duped by North Korean hacker | Information Age | ACS&lt;/a&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 10pt;"&gt;- State sponsored threat actor tricked the usual vetting procedures when hired.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 12pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 10pt;"&gt;5. &lt;a href="https://ia.acs.org.au/article/2025/china-based-backdoor-found-in-health-devices.html?ref=newsletter&amp;amp;deliveryName=DM25242" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 12pt;"&gt;China-based backdoor found in health devices | Information Age | ACS&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; - Medical IoT device&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h5&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Session Topic:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h5&gt;&lt;div&gt;During the session we Investigate common and emerging cyber security attacks, and techniques.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Specifically we will be investigating:&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;ul style="list-style-type: disc;"&gt;&lt;li style="list-style-type: inherit;"&gt;The known Cyber attacks identified and characterised&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li style="list-style-type: inherit;"&gt;How they work, what vulnerabilities are exploited.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;img src="@X@EmbeddedFile.requestUrlStub@X@bbcswebdav/xid-47094945_1" alt="" width="596" height="381" style="border: 0px solid #000000;"&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Then we will examine the Internet of Things (IoT);&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul style="list-style-type: disc;"&gt;&lt;li style="list-style-type: inherit;"&gt;IoT devices are presented&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li style="list-style-type: inherit;"&gt;The reasons for their deployment (why they are used)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li style="list-style-type: inherit;"&gt;The particular problems with ensuring their security, both standalone and on the network.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ul style="list-style-type: disc;"&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;h5&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Out of Session Activity:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h5&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Review the PowerPoint presentations, and the notes provided by your lecturer.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;h5&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Portfolio Tasks:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h5&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="color: #000000; font-size: 13.3333px;"&gt;Check assessments tab.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="color: #000000; font-size: 13.3333px;"&gt;Should be able to complete PART-TWO&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style="font-family: 'Open Sans', sans-serif; text-shadow: none !important; letter-spacing: normal; margin: 0px 0px 1em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-size: small; color: #000000; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</TEXT><TYPE
